<br>
Basically you get out of the guild what you put into it. If you help others get loot, there is a direct reflection on how many points you earn.<br>
<br>
For instance:<br>
<br>
20dkp of loot is purchased at a raid.<br>
<br>
That 20 dkp is split among the people there. There is no DKP inflation, but we do have some DKP drift, which is automatically taken care of as we do DKP adjustments.<br>
<br>
If you are at all familiar with DKP this should make some sense, but if you are a DKP newb (as i was a few months ago) this can sound complicated  =) I love the system we have now. It works great for our casual guild. <p><center>
